  "language": "en",
  "text": "Are you a millionaire? I'm not a millionaire, but according to Forbes, I'm a billionaire. So was the sacrifice worth it to become a billionaire? It wasn't a sacrifice. Why not? The journey is the reward. Remember this, the money does not belong to you. The money belongs to God. This world's going to end like this. And on our last day, we're not going to be talking about money or what deal we didn't do. We're going to be thinking about the time we didn't spend with the people we love. Do you think anybody can become a billionaire? No. Why not? Read a book called Never Eat Alone. Luck doesn't just come. Luck comes when you're looking for opportunity. In our last interview, I asked you, have you ever been fucked over in business before? And I told you, yes I have, but I fuck back. I know you like that. What is the greatest advice you ever received throughout your career? Look, one time a guy named Bill McBride was running for governor and he told me this, your children are one friend away from total disaster. And if you don't separate it when you see it, you can lose your kid. When you lay and sleep with pigs, you get pig shit on you. As a billionaire, would you consider yourself to be smart? I am not smart. And I know I'm not smart, which is very good. I read a book once called Tight About Rockefeller. And in that book, they said he built standard oil. And somebody asked him, how can you build this oil company? You're not a scientist. You're not a geologist. You're a bookkeeper. And here's the line I underlined. I hire scientists. I'm not a smart guy, but I'm smart enough to go find smart guys. How do you know? 69. 69. My favorite number. If I took everything away from you, and all you could keep is one trait, to become a billionaire, make it back, what would that be? Listen, the great circuses, the people came to see the lion and the tiger eat the man in the middle. You know why they don't eat the man in the middle? Because he loves them and feeds them. If you're building a business, think about the guy in the ring and why the lions don't eat him. And when you see the great Wilinda up on the wire, walking without a net, you know why he didn't fall? Focus. Focus, love them and feed them. You've got amazing advice for it. This is awesome. Thank you, Josh. That was great.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 0.7,
      "text": "Are you a millionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1.1,
      "end": 4.4,
      "text": "I'm not a millionaire, but according to Forbes, I'm a billionaire."
    },
    {
      "start": 4.7,
      "end": 6.5,
      "text": "So was the sacrifice worth it to become a billionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 6.8,
      "end": 7.7,
      "text": "It wasn't a sacrifice."
    },
    {
      "start": 8.1,
      "end": 8.3,
      "text": "Why not?"
    },
    {
      "start": 8.5,
      "end": 9.7,
      "text": "The journey is the reward."
    },
    {
      "start": 10.0,
      "end": 12.2,
      "text": "Remember this, the money does not belong to you."
    },
    {
      "start": 12.5,
      "end": 13.6,
      "text": "The money belongs to God."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.9,
      "end": 15.3,
      "text": "This world's going to end like this."
    },
    {
      "start": 15.6,
      "end": 18.2,
      "text": "And on our last day, we're not going to be talking about money"
    },
    {
      "start": 18.2,
      "end": 19.6,
      "text": "or what deal we didn't do."
    },
    {
      "start": 19.7,
      "end": 23.0,
      "text": "We're going to be thinking about the time we didn't spend with the people we love."
    },
    {
      "start": 23.1,
      "end": 24.5,
      "text": "Do you think anybody can become a billionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 24.8,
      "end": 24.9,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 25.1,
      "end": 25.4,
      "text": "Why not?"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.6,
      "end": 27.1,
      "text": "Read a book called Never Eat Alone."
    },
    {
      "start": 27.4,
      "end": 28.2,
      "text": "Luck doesn't just come."
    },
    {
      "start": 28.2,
      "end": 31.6,
      "text": "Luck comes when you're looking for opportunity."
    },
    {
      "start": 31.8,
      "end": 33.3,
      "text": "In our last interview, I asked you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 33.4,
      "end": 35.1,
      "text": "have you ever been fucked over in business before?"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.3,
      "end": 39.4,
      "text": "And I told you, yes I have, but I fuck back."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.2,
      "end": 41.4,
      "text": "I know you like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 41.6,
      "end": 44.2,
      "text": "What is the greatest advice you ever received throughout your career?"
    },
    {
      "start": 44.4,
      "end": 47.0,
      "text": "Look, one time a guy named Bill McBride was running for governor"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.0,
      "end": 51.9,
      "text": "and he told me this, your children are one friend away from total disaster."
    },
    {
      "start": 52.2,
      "end": 54.9,
      "text": "And if you don't separate it when you see it, you can lose your kid."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.9,
      "end": 59.0,
      "text": "When you lay and sleep with pigs, you get pig shit on you."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.2,
      "end": 61.3,
      "text": "As a billionaire, would you consider yourself to be smart?"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.6,
      "end": 62.4,
      "text": "I am not smart."
    },
    {
      "start": 62.5,
      "end": 64.6,
      "text": "And I know I'm not smart, which is very good."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.7,
      "end": 67.4,
      "text": "I read a book once called Tight About Rockefeller."
    },
    {
      "start": 67.6,
      "end": 69.7,
      "text": "And in that book, they said he built standard oil."
    },
    {
      "start": 69.8,
      "end": 72.3,
      "text": "And somebody asked him, how can you build this oil company?"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.5,
      "end": 73.4,
      "text": "You're not a scientist."
    },
    {
      "start": 73.6,
